HEADWORD: Bluethroat
<hw>Blue"throat`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A singing bird of northern Europe and Asia (<spn>Cyanecula
Suecica</spn>), related to the nightingales; -- called also
<altname>blue-throated robin</altname> and <altname>blue-throated
warbler</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bluets</ent>⟦br⟧
